"title": "5682: family, significance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5682",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God created the family and is deeply concerned for its welfare. Scripture uses family metaphors to describe the relationship between God and his people.</p>\n<h2>God created the family</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:6\">PSA 68:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:27\">GEN 1:26–1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:23-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:23–2:24</a></p>\n<h2>God cares for the families of those who honour him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:1\">GEN 7:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:18\">GEN 6:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:8-Deut5:10\">DEU 5:8–5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:11\">2SA 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:18-Jer35:19\">JER 35:18–35:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:17-Jer38:18\">JER 38:17–38:18</a></p>\n<h2>God judges families who disobey him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:4-Exod20:5\">EXO 20:4–20:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:23-Num16:32\">NUM 16:23–16:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:6\">DEU 11:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:24-Josh7:26\">JOS 7:24–7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:12-1Sam3:14\">1SA 3:12–3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:17\">2SA 24:17</a></p>\n<h2>Families in Israel</h2>\n<h3>The extended family was the basic social unit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh7:5\">NEH 7:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:10\">LEV 25:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:16\">LEV 27:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:32\">NUM 2:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:40\">NUM 4:40</a></p>\n<h3>Family heads were community leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:1\">NUM 36:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:4\">NUM 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:26\">NUM 31:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:1\">1KI 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:2\">2CH 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Families had religious obligations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:7\">DEU 12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:22-Exod12:23\">EXO 12:22–12:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:11-Deut12:12\">DEU 12:11–12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:21\">1SA 1:21</a></p>\n<h3>Families were to teach their children God's law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:5-Ps78:7\">PSA 78:5–78:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:19\">GEN 18:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:26-Exod12:27\">EXO 12:26–12:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:9\">DEU 4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:6-Deut6:7\">DEU 6:6–6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:8-Prov1:9\">PRO 1:8–1:9</a></p>\n<h2>The relationship between God and his people described in family metaphors</h2>\n<h3>They are his family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:10\">GAL 6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:1\">AMO 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:15\">EPH 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:17\">1PE 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>They are his children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:1\">DEU 14:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:16\">ISA 63:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1-Hos11:4\">HOS 11:1–11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:15-Rom8:17\">ROM 8:15–8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:4–4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:5\">EPH 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>They are brothers and sisters in God's family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:11\">HEB 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:22\">PSA 22:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:17-Isa8:18\">ISA 8:17–8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:50\">MAT 12:50</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:21\">LUK 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:31-Mark3:34\">MRK 3:31–3:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:12-Heb2:17\">HEB 2:12–2:17</a></p>\n<h2>The salvation of families</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:34\">ACT 16:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:14\">ACT 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:8\">ACT 18:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:16\">1CO 1:16</a></p>\n<h2>Good family management as a qualification for church office</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:4-1Tim3:5\">1TI 3:4–3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:12\">1TI 3:12</a></p>\n<h2>Christians are to support their families</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:8\">1TI 5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:4\">1TI 5:4</a></p>\n<h2>The urgent demands of the kingdom of God should take priority over family responsibilities</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:59-Luke9:60\">LUK 9:59–9:60</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:21-Matt8:22\">MAT 8:21–8:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:31-Mark3:34\">MRK 3:31–3:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:61-Luke9:62\">LUK 9:61–9:62</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:34-Matt10:38\">MAT 10:34–10:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:51-Luke12:53\">LUK 12:51–12:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:6\">MIC 7:6</a></p>",
